Stroids readme
Linux/Unix
You must have SDL and SDL_mixer libraries installed.

Win32
You must have SDL and SDL_mixer libraries installed.
DirectX 8.0 or higher for force feedback.

Nate Griswold - didn't actually do anything
Tony Magro
John Bethencourt
Can you handle it?
download game data files at:http://www.upl.cs.wisc.edu/~anthony/stroids3d_data.tar.gz

or

Run one of the following scripts to automatically download and install the game data
getstroid3ddata.bat - for win32
getstroid3ddata.sh  - for linux

Keys:
W	= Forward
S	= Backward
A	= Left
D	= Right
C	= Camera View
G	= Release/Grab Mouse
J	= Show collision spheres
ESC = Return to Menu
KP9 = Kill 
GameKeyPad +/- = Change Game Speed

Debug:
O/P - change world size
k/l	- increase world number
KP 1 - Kill YourSelf
KP 2 - Kill All Stroids


